summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of two coffee brands, Maxwell House and Nescafé, based on four distinct consumer perceptions. Maxwell House is perceived as "Lazy" by 4% of consumers and as "Fails to plan household purchases and schedules well" by 12%. Conversely, Nescafé is perceived as "Lazy" by a significantly higher 48% and also as "Fails to plan household purchases and schedules well" by 48%. In terms of positive attributes, Maxwell House is seen as "Thrifty" by 16% of consumers, whereas Nescafé is perceived as "Thrifty" by only 4%. A negative perception of "Not a good wife" is attributed to 16% of Nescafé consumers, while 0% of Maxwell House consumers hold this view. The structure is comparative, highlighting differing consumer perceptions across the two brands for each listed characteristic.
